{
  "stem": "9168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Greater parts of the lungs and other internal organs were eaten away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Some of the experimental subjects had to enter the gas chambers and smash small ampules of liquid gas that they were provided, and inhaled vapors with the same result, lungs destroyed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There were 220 victims, and 50 died almost immediately.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The fifth experiment was sulfanilamide, conducted to determine the effectiveness of sulfa.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "These victims included many Polish Catholic priests, who were wounded, the wounds infected with streptococcus, gas gangrene, and tetanus.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then, to simulate battle wounds, wood shavings and ground glass were forced into the wounds, resulting, of course, in intense agony and pain and mutilation, permanent disability, and countless deaths.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The sixth experiment [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was one of the most inhumane, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was bone, muscle, and nerve regeneration and transplantation.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In which whole sections of bone-- whole legs, arms, including scapulas, were removed from healthy victims and attempted to be transplanted to other healthy victims, who, of necessity, had to have the same parts removed for this experiment.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "These were predominantly young Polish women.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This resulted in death, but for those who lived, permanent mutilation and disability.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On December 20, 1946, a 37-year-old Polish woman testified, during one of my turns in the courtroom, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as follows.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have a bit of her testimony, which I have. 'Question-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what happened to you after you were arrested?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Answer-- I was taken to the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
